How to install required files using anaconda 

Step 1: create new anaconda env 

conda create -n name_of_env python=3.8 anaconda

Step 2: activate env

conda activate name_of_env

Step 3: follow upgrading and installing packages as follows:
pip install --upgrade pip
conda install -c conda-forge easydict
#dont use conda install for opencv install incompatible libraries for tensorflow#
pip install opencv-contrib-python
conda install -c anaconda pillow
conda install -c anaconda numpy
conda install -c conda-forge matplotlib
conda install -c anaconda tensorflow-gpu
pip3 install tensorlayer


